parameters.name: DomainName
parameters.description:
The accelerated domain name. You can specify up to 500 domain names in each request. Separate multiple domain names with commas (,).

By default, this operation queries QPS data for all accelerated domain names that belong to your Alibaba Cloud account.

parameters.name: EndTime
parameters.description:
The end of the time range to query. Specify the time in the ISO 8601 standard in the yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ format. The time must be in UTC.

The end time must be later than the start time.

parameters.name: Interval
parameters.description:
The time granularity of the data entries. Unit: seconds.

The time granularity varies with the maximum time range per query. Valid values: 300 (5 minutes), 3600 (1 hour), and 86400 (1 day). For more information, see **Usage notes**.

parameters.name: IspNameEn
parameters.description: The name of the Internet service provider (ISP) for your Alibaba Cloud CDN service. You can call the [DescribeCdnRegionAndIsp](~~91077~~) operation to query ISPs. If you do not specify an ISP, data of all ISPs is queried.

parameters.name: LocationNameEn
parameters.description: The name of the region. You can call the [DescribeCdnRegionAndIsp](~~91077~~) operation to query regions. If you do not specify a region, data in all regions is queried.

parameters.name: StartTime
parameters.description: The beginning of the time range to query. Specify the time in the ISO 8601 standard in the yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ format. The time must be in UTC.
